 Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience 
 2 + years of corporate and/or search firm experience 
 Experience building and utilizing a variety of sourcing plans and tools, including proactive phone and internet research 
 Experience recruiting passive candidates and building networks 
 CRM/ATS experience with sourcing, tracking and managing candidates 
 MS Office experience, including Word, Excel, and Outlook 
 Experience managing and prioritizing multiple searches, projects and client relationships 
 
Amazon's Alexa Recruiting organization is seeking a talented, customer focused Technical Sourcing Recruiter with a passion for delighting both their clients and candidates. You will work with a close-knit, high performing technical recruiting team supporting the Alexa AI teams. This position focuses on driving candidate generation strategies in an effort to engage technical and non-technical candidates. This is a great opportunity to be part of a team that is making an impact on the business by recruiting for innovative technical talent. Successful Technical Sourcers on this team utilize their experience in setting benchmarks, forecasting and tracking against metrics, and prioritizing to hit customer SLAs. They thrive in an innovative, fast-paced environment, can roll up their sleeves, work hard, and have fun to get the job done. They draw on extensive knowledge of Talent Acquisition and functional areas of the business, forging dynamic relationships with business leaders and hiring managers.
 
Key job responsibilities
 Successful candidate on Alexa AI recruiting team utilize their experience to build candidate pipelines utilizing non-traditional sources for technical and non-technical roles, assessing fit and being able to share business compelling story and Employee Value Proposition (EVP).
 
About the team
 The team is a fun recruiting team that is incredibly driven and collaborate with a growing business where you can make a big impact, innovate, and be a part of something big for Amazon. Your work is valued as much as your life outside of work.
 
Amazon is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace. Amazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, age, or other legally protected status. For individuals with disabilities who would like to request an accommodation, please visit https://www.amazon.jobs/en/disability/us.
 
